# MeshCore Signed Plugin Release Flow

When the user provides a signed plugin zip path (TPC/TAK Signed) for **MeshCore**, perform this flow end-to-end:

1. Verify `main` is current and pushed on `atakmaps/TAK-MESHCORE`.
2. Inspect the zip and extract the signed APK (`ATAK-Plugin-Meshcore-*-tpc-5.5.1-civ-release.apk`).
3. Validate APK: `package: com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin`, `versionCode` / `versionName` match release intent.
4. Create/push tag `v<version>` on the release commit; create GitHub Release on **TAK-MESHCORE** with title **`TAK-MeshCore <version>`** (not plain "MeshCore"), signed APK, AAB, and `MeshCore-*-ATAK-5.5.1-source.zip`.
5. **Do not** deploy to `com.uvpro.plugin.apk` — that is UV-PRO only.
6. **Always** upload MeshCore signed APK to cloud:
   - `scp … root@31.220.30.74:/var/www/html/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin.apk`
7. **Always** update MeshCore row in server `generate_infz.py` (`name`: **`TAK-MeshCore`**, plus `version` + `version_code` for `com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin`).
8. Regenerate catalog: `python3 /var/www/html/plugins/generate_infz.py`
9. Mirror: `cp -f /var/www/html/plugins/product.infz /var/www/html/plugins/5.5.1/product.infz`
10. Verify:
    - `product.inf` row for `com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin` matches signed APK hash/size
    - `https://atakmaps.com/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin.apk` → 200
    - `https://atakmaps.com/plugins/5.5.1/plugins/com.atakmaps.meshcore.plugin.apk` → 200
11. Report release URL, SHA256, catalog version, and URLs.

## TPC submission (before signing)

`tools/package-submission.sh` fails unless these are **committed** on `main`:

- `app/src/main/assets/atakmaps-ca.p12`
- `app/src/main/assets/isrg-root-x1.pem`

Same CA bundle as UV-PRO (`atakatak` / `meshcore_trust_bundle_p12_key` in strings.xml).

Prefer explicit verification over assumptions. If any step fails, stop and report the exact blocker.
